Former FBI Director Louis Freeh nearly died last summer when he was involved in a car crash driving near his summer home in Barnard , Vermont .
Current FBI director James Comey and Vermont Senator Patrick Leahy spoke about the accident for the first time .
They say 64-year-old Freeh severed an artery in one of his legs and would have bled to death in just 60 seconds .
Freeh is still recovering from the crash and walking with a cane .